### 🟨 6. **No HTTPS Enforcement (Insecure Communication)**
The app should be configured to always run over HTTPS. Without HTTPS, data in transit is unencrypted, increasing the risk of man-in-the-middle (MITM) attacks.

**Recommendation:**
Add middleware to redirect HTTP requests to HTTPS.

Example (only if you are using Express 4+):
```javascript
const https = require('https');
const fs = require('fs');
const http = require('http');

// Ensure redirect to HTTPS
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  if (req.headers['x-forwarded-proto'] !== 'https') {
    return res.redirect(`https://${req.headers.host}${req.url}`);
  }
  next();
});

// Start HTTPS server if configured
const options = {
  key: fs.readFileSync('key.pem'),
  cert: fs.readFileSync('cert.pem'),
};
const server = https.createServer(options, app);
server.listen(443, () => {
  console.log('HTTPS Server running on port 443');
});
```

